===Talking to Terry===
* '''Player:''' Hello, are you Terry Balando?
* '''Terry Balando:''' That's right, who wants to know...?
* '''Terry Balando:''' Ah yes, I recognise you! You're the fellow who found that strange artefact about Zaros for the museum, aren't you? What can I do for you now?
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the etchings.}}
** '''Player:''' I had some etchings to deliver to you, but I don't have them on me...
** '''Terry Balando:''' Then... you better go get them for me?
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the etchings.}}
** '''Player:''' That's right. I was in the desert down by the Bedabin Camp, and I found an archaeologist who asked me to deliver this to you.
** '''Terry Balando:''' You spoke to the legendary Asgarnia Smith??? Quickly, let me see what he had to give you! He is always at the forefront of archaeological breakthroughs!
** '''Player:''' So what does the inscription say? Anything interesting?
** '''Terry Balando:''' This... this is fascinating! These cuneiforms seem to predate even the settlement we are excavating here... Yes, yes, this is most interesting indeed!
** '''Player:''' Can you translate it for me?
** '''Terry Balando:''' Well, I am not familiar with this particular language, but the similarities inherent in the pictographs seem to show a prevalent trend towards a syllabary consistent with the phonemes we have discovered in this excavation!
** '''Player:''' Um... So, can you translate it for me or not?
** '''Terry Balando:''' Well, unfortunately this is the only example of this particular language I have ever seen, but I might be able to make a rough translation, of sorts...
** '''Terry Balando:''' It might be slightly obscure on the finer details, but it should be good enough to understand the rough meaning of what was originally written. Please, just wait a moment, I will write up what I can
** '''Terry Balando:''' translate into a journal for you. Then you can take it back to Asgarnia, I think he will be extremely interested in the translation!
** {{tact|end}}

