* '''Player:''' Please, if I can just have a few minutes of your time to ask some questions...?
* '''Eblis:''' (sigh) I suppose I can spare you that. What do you wish to know about?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Why is this village so hostile?}}
** '''Player:''' Why are all of the people here so hostile? You would think I was asking you for money instead of just for answers to a few questions...
** '''Eblis:''' It is a long story, and I doubt you have much interest in hearing it. Your sort never are, you just take what you can of ours, and then abandon us once more to the desert.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|No, I want to hear this story.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I'd be quite interested to hear what it is you have to say to excuse the attitude everybody in this village seems to have.
*** '''Eblis:''' Ah, it all begun many generations ago, when our ancestors were the proud rulers of these lands...
*** '''Eblis:''' My ancestors lived far to the North of here, and our lands stretched from the sea in the East to the river Lum, and the mountain of ice. From coast to coast, North to South, our domain was absolute.
*** '''Eblis:''' Our god was kind to us, and blessed us with prosperity and happiness, and in return we were merciless to his enemies wherever we found them.
*** '''Eblis:''' Then came the betrayal.
*** '''Eblis:''' Our god was banished, leaving us helpless to our fates.
*** '''Eblis:''' Without his protection, we were forced to fend for ourselves once more, against the enemies that sought to destroy us through their petty jealousies.
*** '''Eblis:''' But we did not succumb without fighting! The spiteful Saradomin and pathetic Zamorak warred with each other, but the hatred they had for each other was as nothing to the hatred they held towards us!
*** '''Eblis:''' With each battle they waged, we lost more and more land, unable to fight on all fronts, and were pushed further and further South into this gods-forsaken desert.
*** '''Eblis:''' Our greatest hero, Azzanadra, was finally trapped in a strange stone structure to the South of here, and bound within by terrible powers...
*** '''Eblis:''' And with that our lands, our homes, our very lives were stolen from us! Too weak to reclaim what was rightfully ours, we made our homes here, knowing that someday Azzanadra will
*** '''Eblis:''' return with his magnificent power, and bring us back to our former glory...
*** '''Player:''' So you're upset because of something that happened hundreds of years ago?
*** '''Player:''' Seems to me like maybe you should find some closure, and let the past go...
*** '''Eblis:''' The insults heaped upon my race will never be forgotten, will never be forgiven and will never again be overlooked.
*** '''Eblis:''' Someday, a harsh wind will blow upon this land, uncovering the wrongs of the past, and we will get back what is rightfully ours. Until such a day we will bide our time here, and will
*** '''Eblis:''' always be ready with our blades for our righteous vengeance.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|I don't care about your story.}}
*** '''Player:''' I don't really care what your story is to be honest, there is no excuse for such rudeness or hostility.
*** '''Player:''' I have done nothing wrong to you, but everybody here treats me like I have committed some great crime against the village.
*** '''Eblis:''' That is because, from our point of view, you have.
*** '''Player:''' What? Just because I entered your village?
*** '''Eblis:''' You have no right to be here! You have no right to the life you have, for it was taken at our expense!
*** '''Player:''' Whatever... No wonder all you loonies live out here in the desert by yourselves.
*** {{tact|end}}
